attributes.magic: PE32 executable (GUI) Intel 80386, for MS Windows

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Identifies another 64 bit API hashing function used by Metasploit.
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: Elastic Security

crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Identifies Metasploit 64 bit reverse tcp shellcode.
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: Elastic Security

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a position-independent stager shellcode. It dynamically resolves API functions by walking the Process Environment Block (PEB) and hashing module/function names (ROR-13 algorithm). It resolves networking functions like 'connect' (hash 0x6174a599) and 'recv' (hash 0x5fc8d902) from ws2_32.dll, and memory management functions like 'VirtualAlloc' (hash 0xe0df0fea) and 'VirtualProtect' (hash 0x300f2f0b). This behavior is characteristic of a downloader or reverse shell that connects to a remote server to fetch and execute a second-stage payload.
